Interdepartmental Network Connectivity: Sales & Marketing

Overview
This project establishes a basic network infrastructure that enables seamless communication 
between the Sales and Marketing departments. Using Cisco Packet Tracer, the design demonstrates how two 
separate departments can be interconnected through proper switching, routing, and cabling.

Project Features
-1 Router, 2 Access Switches, and 4 End Devices
-Two PCs assigned to the Sales department
-Two PCs assigned to the Marketing department
-Correct cable types and interface configurations
-Device IP addressing and interdepartmental routing
-Connectivity testing using ICMP (ping)

Files Included
-PacketTracer/Interdepartmental Network Design for Sales and Marketing.pkt
Cisco Packet Tracer file containing the full network topology
-Documentation.docx
Project documentation explaining design considerations, configuration steps, and testing results

How to Use
-Download the .pkt file from the repository.
-Open it in Cisco Packet Tracer 
Verify communication by:
-Pinging between devices within the Sales department
-Pinging between devices within the Marketing department
-Pinging across departments (Sales â†” Marketing) to confirm full interdepartmental connectivity
